               <head>Adab-e ‘Abbasi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ādāb-i ʿAbbāsī by Ṣadr al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Tabrīzī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112936 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85114211 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85067900 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85018837" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f4193">Ṣadr al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Tabrīzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f4193">صدر الدّين محمّد التّبريزى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_10829">Ādāb-i ʿAbbāsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_10829">آداب عبّاسى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Compendium of Twelver Shīʿī etiquette, ritual and elective prayers in accordance with the 24-hour diurnal and nocturnal cycle divided into 6 uneven periods, each has a chapter or bāb devoted to it, here translated from the Arabic work Miftāḥ al-falāḥ attributed to Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ʿĀmilī (1547-1621) by Ṣadr al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Tabrīzī and named after, if not dedicated to, Shāh ʿAbbās I. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Neat scribal naskh with copious annotations in red shikastah. </p>
                        <p>Detached leather binding, delaminating and damaged by wormholes. </p>
                        <p>Oblong octagonal seal impression (f. 1v): Ṭufayl Muḥammad-i Murād ʿAlī 12[3?]7/1821-2. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
